---
name: scljet-sql-mutation-count
description: SclJet executeMutationCounted — affected-row count + last INSERT rowid; matches reference sqlite3 changes()/last_insert_rowid()
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet counted mutations

`executeMutationCounted(db, sql)` runs a DML/DDL statement and returns a `MutationResult(image,
changes, lastInsertRowid)`. `changes` matches sqlite's `changes()`: #value-tuples for INSERT,
#rows-matching-WHERE for UPDATE/DELETE, 0 for CREATE/DROP. `lastInsertRowid` is the highest rowid
assigned by an INSERT (scljet assigns sequential rowids from maxRowid+1), and 0 for non-INSERT
statements (the caller persists the previous value). The affected-row counts were checked against
reference sqlite3 out-of-band; locked across backends. This is the engine addition the JDBC
`executeUpdate`/`getGeneratedKeys` façade depends on.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[executeMutationCounted, MutationResult](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def step(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutationCounted(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(r) =>
      println(sql + " => changes=" + r.changes.toString + " rowid=" + r.lastInsertRowid.toString)
      r.image

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann")),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob")),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val d1 = step(db0, "INSERT INTO emp VALUES (10,'dan'),(11,'eve')")
    val d2 = step(d1, "UPDATE emp SET name='X' WHERE id >= 2")
    val d3 = step(d2, "DELETE FROM emp WHERE id >= 10")
    val d4 = step(d3, "CREATE TABLE t(x INTEGER)")
    println("done")
```
